The Mission, led by the Western Cape Government and Wesgro, aims to strengthen Western Cape-Japan and Western Cape-Singapore partnerships in a number of key priority areas, including trade, investment, tourism, agri-processing and renewable energy. A Trade, Investment and Tourism seminar will be held in each market attracting key local government and business stakeholders. Joshin Raghubar, chairman of CiTi and the Bandwidth Barn commented, &#x201c;CiTi welcomes this opportunity to engage with leading businesses and investors in the fintech and technology space while promoting Cape Town&#x2019;s position as the leading tech hub in Africa.&#x201d; Singapore is viewed as a major upcoming fintech market providing exposure and massive learning opportunities for the local technology economy. For more, contact az.gro.itic&#64;zan .